  "text": "Treatment with HDAC Inhibitors. NaBT (Sigma, St. Louis, MO) was dissolved in PBS, and suberoylanilide hydroxamic acid was dissolved in DMSO. Cells were treated from 0 to 4 days and at the doses indicated. Treatment groups were compared with vehicle controls. Caffeic acid, a 15-lipoxygenase-1 inhibitor, was used at a concentration of 2.2 mol/L. The specificity of this concentration has been previously established for inhibiting 15-lipoxygenase-1 in colorectal cancer cells [CITATION_1] . Nordihydroguaiaretic acid, a general lipoxygenase inhibitor, was used at a concentration of 10 mol/L. Cells were harvested at the various time points indicated.",
